author: rhuijben
msg: Remove another loggy operation by moving support for setting an explicit
modification time into the existing record_fileinfo wq operation.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/log.c
(SVN_WC__LOG_SET_TIMESTAMP,
SVN_WC__LOG_ATTR_TIMESTAMP): Remove defines.
(log_do_file_timestamp): Remove function.
(start_handler): Remove support for set_timestamp.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/log.h
(svn_wc__loggy_set_timestamp): Remove function.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c
(file_baton): Document that last_changed_date will be NULL when
use-commit-times is not enabled.
(change_file_prop): Rename pool to scratch_pool. Reorder if to cheapest
first. Don't copy a value that we already copied to the right pool.
(merge_file): Pass date to record_fileinfo instead of adding a new loggy
item. Update comment to answer its former question.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/workqueue.c
(run_record_fileinfo): Parse optional argument and use it to set the mtime
if local_abspath specifies an existing file.
(svn_wc__wq_build_record_fileinfo): Add time to set to skel
* subversion/libsvn_wc/workqueue.h
(svn_wc__wq_build_record_fileinfo): Add explicit time argument.
